<h3 class="subhead linespace">Genesis 1:4 Context</h3>
<br /><p class='pspace' style='color:#666'><a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-1/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth."><sup class='graytxt'>1</sup></a>In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth. <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-2/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness [was] upon the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters."><sup class='graytxt'>2</sup></a>And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness <em>was</em> upon the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters. <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-3/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And God said, Let there be light: and there was light."><sup class='graytxt'>3</sup></a>And God said, Let there be light: and there was light. <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-4/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And God saw the light, that [it was] good: and God divided the light from the darkness."><sup class='graytxt'>4</sup></a><strong class='highlight'>And God saw the light, that <em>it was</em> good: and God divided the light from the darkness.</strong> <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-5/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And the evening and the morning were the first day."><sup class='graytxt'>5</sup></a>And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And the evening and the morning were the first day. <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-6/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters."><sup class='graytxt'>6</sup></a>And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters. <a href="https://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Genesis-1-7/" title="CLICK FOR MORE TRANSLATIONS of Genesis 1:4- And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which [were] under the firmament from the waters which [were] above the firmament: and it was so."><sup class='graytxt'>7</sup></a>And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which <em>were</em> under the firmament from the waters which <em>were</em> above the firmament: and it was so. </p><br>
